node.text: Love the edit! How did you land on this style for this image? 😍🔥

Face to face with this cheeky girl 🦈

Something you may not know about tiger sharks 👇🏽 

These sharks exhibit a level of curiosity and investigative behaviour that sets them apart from many other shark species. Unlike great whites, which often use a ‘bite and release’ strategy to assess prey, tiger sharks tend to approach things including boats, divers, and even floating debris with slow, deliberate movements and gentle nudges before deciding whether to investigate further or not.

Their nocturnal instincts make these sharks more active and bolder at night, but in Fuvahmulah, where they are encountered on a daily basis, they display a greater level of predictability (compared to other tiger shark aggregation sites of the world) and we even see individual personality differences in how they interact with the divers!

These sharks are just the coolest and forever my favourite underwater animal 🩵

Ps. As always, swipe to see before editing 👉🏽
